{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":834,"text":"So my moment of truth"},{"time":2872,"text":"did not come all at once."},{"time":5936,"text":"In 2010, I had the chance to be considered"},{"time":9562,"text":"for promotion from my job"},{"time":11889,"text":"as director of policy planning"},{"time":13961,"text":"at the U.S. State Department."},{"time":16718,"text":"This was my moment to lean in,"},{"time":20449,"text":"to push myself forward"},{"time":23334,"text":"for what are really only a handful"},{"time":26028,"text":"of the very top foreign policy jobs,"},{"time":29045,"text":"and I had just finished a big, 18-month project"},{"time":32125,"text":"for Secretary Clinton, successfully,"},{"time":34698,"text":"and I knew I could handle a bigger job."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38929,"text":"The woman I thought I was"},{"time":42759,"text":"would have said yes."},{"time":44930,"text":"But I had been commuting for two years"},{"time":46957,"text":"between Washington and Princeton, New Jersey,"},{"time":50100,"text":"where my husband and my two teenage sons lived,"},{"time":54027,"text":"and it was not going well."},{"time":57293,"text":"I tried on the idea of eking out another two years"},{"time":60998,"text":"in Washington, or maybe uprooting my sons"},{"time":63794,"text":"from their school and my husband from his work"},{"time":65929,"text":"and asking them to join me."},{"time":68510,"text":"But deep down, I knew"},{"time":71549,"text":"that the right decision was to go home,"},{"time":75080,"text":"even if I didn't fully recognize the woman"},{"time":77996,"text":"who was making that choice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81988,"text":"That was a decision based on love"},{"time":85495,"text":"and responsibility."},{"time":87439,"text":"I couldn't keep watching my oldest son"},{"time":90338,"text":"make bad choices"},{"time":91763,"text":"without being able to be there for him"},{"time":94458,"text":"when and if he needed me."},{"time":98241,"text":"But the real change came more gradually."},{"time":101755,"text":"Over the next year,"},{"time":103514,"text":"while my family was righting itself,"},{"time":106389,"text":"I started to realize"},{"time":108053,"text":"that even if I could go back into government,"},{"time":110992,"text":"I didn't want to."},{"time":112772,"text":"I didn't want to miss the last five years"},{"time":116719,"text":"that my sons were at home."},{"time":119551,"text":"I finally allowed myself to accept"},{"time":123437,"text":"what was really most important to me,"},{"time":126443,"text":"not what I was conditioned to want"},{"time":129852,"text":"or maybe what I conditioned myself to want,"},{"time":134550,"text":"and that decision led to a reassessment"},{"time":139611,"text":"of the feminist narrative that I grew up with"},{"time":142634,"text":"and have always championed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146290,"text":"I am still completely committed"},{"time":150142,"text":"to the cause of male-female equality,"},{"time":155327,"text":"but let's think about what that equality really means,"},{"time":160273,"text":"and how best to achieve it."},{"time":163200,"text":"I always accepted the idea"},{"time":166323,"text":"that the most respected and powerful people"},{"time":169248,"text":"in our society are men at the top of their careers,"},{"time":173753,"text":"so that the measure of male-female equality"},{"time":177928,"text":"ought to be how many women are in those positions:"},{"time":182147,"text":"prime ministers, presidents, CEOs,"},{"time":185066,"text":"directors, managers, Nobel laureates, leaders."},{"time":190169,"text":"I still think we should do everything we possibly can"},{"time":194446,"text":"to achieve that goal."},{"time":196526,"text":"But that's only half of real equality,"},{"time":201651,"text":"and I now think we're never going to get there"},{"time":204999,"text":"unless we recognize the other half."},{"time":210281,"text":"I suggest that real equality,"},{"time":214592,"text":"full equality,"},{"time":216863,"text":"does not just mean valuing women"},{"time":220078,"text":"on male terms."},{"time":222245,"text":"It means creating a much wider range"},{"time":226863,"text":"of equally respected choices"},{"time":230875,"text":"for women and for men."},{"time":233926,"text":"And to get there, we have to change our workplaces,"},{"time":237395,"text":"our policies and our culture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240309,"text":"In the workplace,"},{"time":242374,"text":"real equality means valuing family"},{"time":245677,"text":"just as much as work,"},{"time":247300,"text":"and understanding that the two reinforce each other."},{"time":251863,"text":"As a leader and as a manager,"},{"time":253766,"text":"I have always acted on the mantra,"},{"time":256811,"text":"if family comes first,"},{"time":259091,"text":"work does not come second --"},{"time":261938,"text":"life comes together."},{"time":264242,"text":"If you work for me, and you have a family issue,"},{"time":268407,"text":"I expect you to attend to it,"},{"time":270841,"text":"and I am confident,"},{"time":272486,"text":"and my confidence has always been borne out,"},{"time":275183,"text":"that the work will get done, and done better."},{"time":279174,"text":"Workers who have a reason to get home"},{"time":281575,"text":"to care for their children or their family members"},{"time":284954,"text":"are more focused, more efficient,"},{"time":287461,"text":"more results-focused."},{"time":289484,"text":"And breadwinners who are also caregivers"},{"time":292613,"text":"have a much wider range"},{"time":295220,"text":"of experiences and contacts."},{"time":297746,"text":"Think about a lawyer who spends part of his time"},{"time":300978,"text":"at school events for his kids"},{"time":303579,"text":"talking to other parents."},{"time":305405,"text":"He's much more likely to bring in"},{"time":307463,"text":"new clients for his firm"},{"time":309403,"text":"than a lawyer who never leaves his office."},{"time":312664,"text":"And caregiving itself"},{"time":314553,"text":"develops patience --"},{"time":318335,"text":"a lot of patience --"},{"time":320798,"text":"and empathy, creativity, resilience, adaptability."},{"time":326418,"text":"Those are all attributes that are ever more important"},{"time":330216,"text":"in a high-speed, horizontal,"},{"time":332309,"text":"networked global economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336758,"text":"The best companies actually know this."},{"time":339946,"text":"The companies that win awards"},{"time":341673,"text":"for workplace flexibility in the United States"},{"time":344925,"text":"include some of our most successful corporations,"},{"time":348151,"text":"and a 2008 national study"},{"time":350422,"text":"on the changing workforce"},{"time":352475,"text":"showed that employees"},{"time":354089,"text":"in flexible and effective workplaces"},{"time":357591,"text":"are more engaged with their work,"},{"time":359304,"text":"they're more satisfied and more loyal,"},{"time":361794,"text":"they have lower levels of stress"},{"time":363627,"text":"and higher levels of mental health."},{"time":366026,"text":"And a 2012 study of employers"},{"time":369736,"text":"showed that deep, flexible practices"},{"time":372589,"text":"actually lowered operating costs"},{"time":374979,"text":"and increased adaptability"},{"time":377444,"text":"in a global service economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380531,"text":"So you may think"},{"time":383648,"text":"that the privileging of work over family"},{"time":387865,"text":"is only an American problem."},{"time":391812,"text":"Sadly, though, the obsession with work"},{"time":395350,"text":"is no longer a uniquely American disease."},{"time":398510,"text":"Twenty years ago,"},{"time":400282,"text":"when my family first started going to Italy,"},{"time":402278,"text":"we used to luxuriate in the culture of siesta."},{"time":405881,"text":"Siesta is not just about avoiding the heat of the day."},{"time":408764,"text":"It's actually just as much"},{"time":410630,"text":"about embracing the warmth of a family lunch."},{"time":413742,"text":"Now, when we go, fewer and fewer businesses"},{"time":416945,"text":"close for siesta,"},{"time":418658,"text":"reflecting the advance of global corporations"},{"time":422196,"text":"and 24-hour competition."},{"time":425033,"text":"So making a place for those we love"},{"time":427902,"text":"is actually a global imperative."}]},{"cues":[{"time":431647,"text":"In policy terms,"},{"time":434377,"text":"real equality means recognizing"},{"time":437813,"text":"that the work that women have traditionally done"},{"time":440771,"text":"is just as important"},{"time":442648,"text":"as the work that men have traditionally done,"},{"time":445311,"text":"no matter who does it."},{"time":448363,"text":"Think about it: Breadwinning and caregiving"},{"time":452108,"text":"are equally necessary for human survival."},{"time":455633,"text":"At least if we get beyond a barter economy,"},{"time":459117,"text":"somebody has to earn an income"},{"time":461354,"text":"and someone else has to convert that income"},{"time":464308,"text":"to care and sustenance for loved ones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":468092,"text":"Now most of you, when you hear me"},{"time":470230,"text":"talk about breadwinning and caregiving,"},{"time":472955,"text":"instinctively translate those categories"},{"time":476396,"text":"into men's work and women's work."},{"time":480127,"text":"And we don't typically challenge"},{"time":482963,"text":"why men's work is advantaged."},{"time":486861,"text":"But consider a same-sex couple"},{"time":489451,"text":"like my friends Sarah and Emily."},{"time":491470,"text":"They're psychiatrists."},{"time":493338,"text":"They got married five years ago,"},{"time":495167,"text":"and now they have two-year-old twins."},{"time":498448,"text":"They love being mothers,"},{"time":500520,"text":"but they also love their work,"},{"time":502088,"text":"and they're really good at what they do."},{"time":504298,"text":"So how are they going to divide up"},{"time":506319,"text":"breadwinning and caregiving responsibilities?"},{"time":508796,"text":"Should one of them stop working"},{"time":510881,"text":"or reduce hours to be home?"},{"time":513573,"text":"Or should they both change their practices"},{"time":516252,"text":"so they can have much more flexible schedules?"},{"time":519535,"text":"And what criteria should they use"},{"time":521506,"text":"to make that decision?"},{"time":522800,"text":"Is it who makes the most money"},{"time":524574,"text":"or who is most committed to her career?"},{"time":528351,"text":"Or who has the most flexible boss?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":532912,"text":"The same-sex perspective helps us see"},{"time":536237,"text":"that juggling work and family"},{"time":538701,"text":"are not women's problems,"},{"time":540812,"text":"they're family problems."},{"time":543450,"text":"And Sarah and Emily are the lucky ones,"},{"time":546473,"text":"because they have a choice"},{"time":548242,"text":"about how much they want to work."},{"time":550779,"text":"Millions of men and women"},{"time":553608,"text":"have to be both breadwinners and caregivers"},{"time":556945,"text":"just to earn the income they need,"},{"time":560485,"text":"and many of those workers are scrambling."},{"time":563033,"text":"They're patching together care arrangements"},{"time":565917,"text":"that are inadequate"},{"time":567090,"text":"and often actually unsafe."},{"time":569501,"text":"If breadwinning and caregiving are really equal,"},{"time":574191,"text":"then why shouldn't a government"},{"time":575779,"text":"invest as much in an infrastructure of care"},{"time":579595,"text":"as the foundation of a healthy society"},{"time":583454,"text":"as it invests in physical infrastructure"},{"time":586566,"text":"as the backbone of a successful economy?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":590442,"text":"The governments that get it --"},{"time":592778,"text":"no surprises here --"},{"time":594625,"text":"the governments that get it,"},{"time":596465,"text":"Norway, Sweden, Denmark, the Netherlands,"},{"time":601170,"text":"provide universal child care,"},{"time":604100,"text":"support for caregivers at home,"},{"time":606219,"text":"school and early childhood education,"},{"time":609386,"text":"protections for pregnant women,"},{"time":611596,"text":"and care for the elderly and the disabled."},{"time":615981,"text":"Those governments invest in that infrastructure"},{"time":619662,"text":"the same way they invest in roads and bridges"},{"time":622991,"text":"and tunnels and trains."},{"time":626126,"text":"Those societies also show you"},{"time":628534,"text":"that breadwinning and caregiving"},{"time":630824,"text":"reinforce each other."},{"time":633208,"text":"They routinely rank among the top 15 countries"},{"time":639047,"text":"of the most globally competitive economies,"},{"time":642380,"text":"but at the same time,"},{"time":644032,"text":"they rank very high on the OECD Better Life Index."},{"time":648723,"text":"In fact, they rank higher than other governments,"},{"time":652259,"text":"like my own, the U.S., or Switzerland,"},{"time":654928,"text":"that have higher average levels of income"},{"time":657857,"text":"but lower rankings on work-life balance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663620,"text":"So changing our workplaces"},{"time":666296,"text":"and building infrastructures of care"},{"time":669592,"text":"would make a big difference,"},{"time":671067,"text":"but we're not going to get equally valued choices"},{"time":675551,"text":"unless we change our culture,"},{"time":678056,"text":"and the kind of cultural change required"},{"time":681197,"text":"means re-socializing men."},{"time":683952,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":687626,"text":"Increasingly in developed countries,"},{"time":689361,"text":"women are socialized to believe that our place"},{"time":692443,"text":"is no longer only in the home,"},{"time":696103,"text":"but men are actually still where they always were."},{"time":700999,"text":"Men are still socialized to believe"},{"time":704397,"text":"that they have to be breadwinners,"},{"time":706652,"text":"that to derive their self-worth"},{"time":709527,"text":"from how high they can climb over other men"},{"time":712406,"text":"on a career ladder."},{"time":714751,"text":"The feminist revolution still has a long way to go."},{"time":717534,"text":"It's certainly not complete."},{"time":719436,"text":"But 60 years after"},{"time":721092,"text":"\"The Feminine\nMystique\" was published,"},{"time":723402,"text":"many women actually have"},{"time":725703,"text":"more choices than men do."},{"time":728681,"text":"We can decide to be a breadwinner,"},{"time":731409,"text":"a caregiver, or any combination of the two."},{"time":735556,"text":"When a man, on the other hand,"},{"time":738082,"text":"decides to be a caregiver,"},{"time":740971,"text":"he puts his manhood on the line."},{"time":744275,"text":"His friends may praise his decision,"},{"time":747495,"text":"but underneath, they're scratching their heads."},{"time":751367,"text":"Isn't the measure of a man"},{"time":754468,"text":"his willingness to compete with other men"},{"time":757399,"text":"for power and prestige?"},{"time":759779,"text":"And as many women hold that view as men do."},{"time":763875,"text":"We know that lots of women"},{"time":766841,"text":"still judge the attractiveness of a man"},{"time":770160,"text":"based in large part on how successful he is"},{"time":772885,"text":"in his career."},{"time":774382,"text":"A woman can drop out of the work force"},{"time":776733,"text":"and still be an attractive partner."},{"time":778893,"text":"For a man, that's a risky proposition."},{"time":783432,"text":"So as parents and partners,"},{"time":785673,"text":"we should be socializing our sons"},{"time":788860,"text":"and our husbands"},{"time":791311,"text":"to be whatever they want to be,"},{"time":794635,"text":"either caregivers or breadwinners."},{"time":798254,"text":"We should be socializing them to make caregiving"},{"time":801610,"text":"cool for guys."},{"time":803597,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":807362,"text":"I can almost hear lots of you thinking, \"No way.\""},{"time":813674,"text":"But in fact, the change is \nactually already happening."},{"time":818321,"text":"At least in the United States,"},{"time":820278,"text":"lots of men take pride in cooking,"},{"time":822502,"text":"and frankly obsess over stoves."},{"time":825818,"text":"They are in the birthing rooms."},{"time":828805,"text":"They take paternity leave when they can."},{"time":831449,"text":"They can walk a baby or soothe a toddler"},{"time":833911,"text":"just as well as their wives can,"},{"time":836553,"text":"and they are increasingly"},{"time":838302,"text":"doing much more of the housework."},{"time":840869,"text":"Indeed, there are male college students now"},{"time":842957,"text":"who are starting to say,"},{"time":844484,"text":"\"I want to be a stay-at-home dad.\""},{"time":846360,"text":"That was completely unthinkable"},{"time":848611,"text":"50 or even 30 years ago."},{"time":851478,"text":"And in Norway, where men have"},{"time":854369,"text":"an automatic three month's paternity leave,"},{"time":857158,"text":"but they lose it if they decide not to take it,"},{"time":860495,"text":"a high government official told me"},{"time":862420,"text":"that companies are starting to look"},{"time":864652,"text":"at prospective male employees"},{"time":866737,"text":"and raise an eyebrow if they didn't in fact"},{"time":870715,"text":"take their leave when they had kids."},{"time":873111,"text":"That means that it's starting to seem"},{"time":875940,"text":"like a character defect"},{"time":878142,"text":"not to want to be a fully engaged father."}]},{"cues":[{"time":885421,"text":"So I was raised"},{"time":890943,"text":"to believe that championing women's rights"},{"time":894592,"text":"meant doing everything we could"},{"time":896711,"text":"to get women to the top."},{"time":898485,"text":"And I still hope that I live long enough"},{"time":901204,"text":"to see men and women equally represented"},{"time":904467,"text":"at all levels of the work force."},{"time":907514,"text":"But I've come to believe that we have to value family"},{"time":911613,"text":"every bit as much as we value work,"},{"time":914445,"text":"and that we should entertain the idea"},{"time":916957,"text":"that doing right by those we love"},{"time":920506,"text":"will make all of us better at everything we do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":924422,"text":"Thirty years ago, Carol Gilligan,"},{"time":926490,"text":"a wonderful psychologist, studied adolescent girls"},{"time":929447,"text":"and identified an ethic of care,"},{"time":932504,"text":"an element of human nature every bit as important"},{"time":935659,"text":"as the ethic of justice."},{"time":937646,"text":"It turns out that \"you don't care\""},{"time":940951,"text":"is just as much a part of who we are"},{"time":943872,"text":"as \"that's not fair.\""},{"time":946152,"text":"Bill Gates agrees."},{"time":947952,"text":"He argues that the two great forces of human nature"},{"time":951123,"text":"are self-interest and caring for others."},{"time":955330,"text":"Let's bring them both together."},{"time":957972,"text":"Let's make the feminist revolution"},{"time":960631,"text":"a humanist revolution."},{"time":963363,"text":"As whole human beings,"},{"time":965107,"text":"we will be better caregivers and breadwinners."},{"time":968951,"text":"You may think that can't happen,"},{"time":971059,"text":"but I grew up in a society"},{"time":972759,"text":"where my mother put out small vases"},{"time":975105,"text":"of cigarettes for dinner parties,"},{"time":977767,"text":"where blacks and whites used separate bathrooms,"},{"time":981960,"text":"and where everybody claimed to be heterosexual."},{"time":988602,"text":"Today, not so much."},{"time":993041,"text":"The revolution for human equality"},{"time":996681,"text":"can happen."},{"time":998471,"text":"It is happening."},{"time":1000717,"text":"It will happen."},{"time":1002999,"text":"How far and how fast is up to us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1007717,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1009860,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}